\kerning1\ul\b\fs28 AStar (class)\kerning0\ulnone\b0\fs24\par
\kerning1 Implements: WSConstants\kerning0\par
\kerning1\i AStar is an implementation of the A* algorithm for pathfinding. This implementation operates on a boolean map (true = passable, false = impassable). It is primarily intended to be called with path().\kerning0\i0\par
\par
\kerning1\i Note: AStar uses AStarNode and AStarOpenList, which should not be directly called by the application programmer during normal use. As such, they are not documented here.\kerning0\i0\par
\par
