\kerning1\ul\b\fs28 BinarySpacePartitioning (static class)\kerning0\ulnone\b0\fs24\par
\kerning1\i This class is entirely static. Its intended purpose is to execute binary space partitioning on an area defined by partition(). It returns a list of all rooms, not just the final rooms, with the first being representing the total space and each subsequent pair representing sibilings. Which is to say, every pair of rooms n and n+1, with n being odd and greater than zero, are adjacent. See full algorithm at {\lang255{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK http://roguebasin.roguelikedevelopment.org/index.php?title=Basic_BSP_Dungeon_generation }}{\fldrslt{http://roguebasin.roguelikedevelopment.org/index.php?title=Basic_BSP_Dungeon_generation\ul0\cf0}}}}\kerning0\i0\f0\fs24 . \par
